     - I think TaskManager and TaskStorage are related because TaskManager needs to first load tasks to be able to orchastrate program logic. For example, to be able to update a task or mark as complete.
     - The `update()` appears to represent the updating logic of a single task by looping throught know properties on the task and matching it with the property the user wants to update, and only updates those properties that are know.  

    Could you, as a senior developer:
    1. Validate my current understanding, correcting any misconceptions
